nodes.title: Post-processing
widgets_values:
| Feature | Default / Example | Description |
|--------:|------------------:|------------:|
| Color match | off | This will try to match the color from the initial image to the samples. The color match algorithms default is set by default to '0.75'. Feel free to test other strength. |
| Perfect loop | off | This can be used with FLF2V or I2V. It will try to find the seamless frame to loop back to the start and blending frames together. üí° Best used with "color match". Try using more frames, e.g. higher seconds. Sometimes FLV2V will morph. |
| Interpolation | off | This will interpolate your video to double fps at the end. Interpolated FPS = 2 √ó FPS. |
| Upscale 2x (fast) | off | Final resolution = 2 √ó start resolution while maintaining aspect ratio. No morph; color-correct fast lanczos upscale. Low VRAM consumption. |
| Upscale /w Model (slow) | off | Final resolution depends on the used upscaler model; Can change/enhance details and high VRAM consumption. |
| Watermark | off | Enable for a watermark overlay on video. |
| Extract Last Frame | off | Enable to extract the last frame of the video as image. |
| MiniMeme | off | This will create a mini gif from your video down scaled by 5 for meme's or discord. |

nodes.title: Resolution note
widgets_values:
### Automatic scaling and resolution calculation The initial image will be scaled on optimized math targeting a WAN 2.2 VAE (div16) resolution. Aspect will be calculated automatically and the video resolution will be set to the nearest possible match with the megapixel count. | Stage | Target MP | Quality | Use case | |---:|---:|---:|---| | 1 | 0.25 | Preview
~ 360p| Motion/physics tests. | | 2 | 0.33 | Fast
~ 432p| Simple quality. | | 3 | 0.40 | SD Speed
~ 480p| "Sweet spot" for speed. | | 4 | 0.60 | SD
~ 576p| Optimal for mobile-first content. | | 5 | 0.72 | Balanced HD
~ 640p| Consistent, good details. | | 6 | 0.85 | HD
~ 720p| Very stable, crisp details. | | 7 | 1.05 | THD
~ 768p| Maximum stability for Image-to-Video. | | 8 | 1.15 | THD+
~ 800p| 16GB VRAM "sweet spot". 16fps/5s | | 9 | 1.30 | HQ
~ 900p| High detail, very slow (Requires high VRAM). | | 10 | 2.07 | FHD
~ 1080p| Production grade detail, extreme slow (Requires very high VRAM). | | 99 | no-scale | equal image | No resolution scaling, like for chaining videos or using last-frame as new input. |

widgets_values:
| Setting | Default / Example | Description | |--------:|------------------:|------------:| | Seconds | 5 | Set the desired length of the video in seconds. | | CRF | 20, webm, VP9 | Video compression level. Visually lossless. Set on VHS Node.| | FPS | 16 | Frames per second for videos. Use 24 for faster motion/shorter videos. | | Shift | 5 | Adjust and test; WAN 2.2 valid in range 5‚Äì10. | | Steps total | 4 | Total steps - node handles step math. More steps ‚Üí higher quality but longer generation. Use even numbers. | | Step Refiner | 2 | Default 2 (50% of 4). Change to test different swap behavior. | | CFG | 1.0 | Controls prompt adherence. Use 1-1.5. 1 disables/ignores the negative prompt. 1.0 is needed for speed-up's like 4/8-step models/LoRAs | | Sampler | euler | "Euler" works every time. Other samplers can enhance detail or motion. This has major impact on how the video is generated. | | Scheduler | simple | "Simple" works every time. Others like "beta" and others can enhance some samplers. | | Seed | number + randomize | Random outcome every run. Set a specific seed to reproduce the same outcome. | | Sage Attention | disabled | Can be enabled **if installed correctly** to speed-up video generation times. | | Watermark upload | none | Here you can upload a watermark image and calibrate the settings to your liking (subgraph). | | Positive prompt | none | Write your positive prompt!
1) Brief description of the setting/appearance
2) Actions, motions, story
3) Camera composition
CFG 1 normally disables/ignores the negative prompt! NAG effectively enables negative prompting on CFG 1.| | Negative prompt | none | Write what you would like to exclude. Works only if CFG > 1 or NAG is enabled | | Checkpoints | Safetensors/GGUf |Choose the type of Checkpoint to use. Wan 2.2 uses a different diffusion model for the first steps (high noise) vs the last steps (low noise). You can ether use safetensors or gguf.| | VAE | same as WAN 2.1 | Still using the same VAE as WAN 2.1. | | CLIP | standard encoder | Use your preferred standard CLIP text encoder. No CLIP Vision H ‚Äî not trained/implemented in WAN 2.2 and weights are disabled. | | Upscaler model | any | The optional used model for Upscaling /w model. A downloaded upscaling-model is needed. | | video_combine_x | empty | Choose the videos for the video combine feature. | | extra_batches_extend_s2v | 1 | If the "Extend S2V" feature is enables and S2V engine is used this will extend the batches for the video with the set number and same frame count as the first batch. | | upload file | none | Upload buttons for any needed extra file like watermark, soundmark and example audio. |

nodes.title: Seconds and frames
widgets_values:
The optimal frame count is calculated automatically based on input seconds.

* **16 FPS** - 5 seconds are native. After that WAN 2.2 starts looping back
* **24 FPS** - 3 seconds are native. After that WAN 2.2 starts looping back.

Both equals the standard frame length of WAN 2.2.

nodes.title: Basic usage
widgets_values:
### üìö READ ME The workflow can combine various features and engines to produce a desired output, but not all combinations can technically work.
‚ö†Ô∏è If a setting combination gives you errors, try to set other switches.
‚ùå Most combinations should automatically disable unwanted combinations.
## Initial setup 0. Download and place needed models and files 1. Select an **engine** you want to use, only 1Ô∏è‚É£ engine should be active at any time ### Usage i2v / flf2v + Audio features 1. Enable the type with the type switch - i2v or flf2v - (optional) Enable fitting **Rendering features** with the rendering switch - (optional) Add LoRAs - (optional) Enable 1 **Audio feature** - (optional) Enable any or multiple **Post-processing features** 2. Choose a resolution **R01-99** for your output 3. Check/Tune any parameter to your liking under **SETTINGS** on the **Backend** panel - Check and set the checkpoints you want to use inside the frontpanel or backends - You need only the checkpoints/models you enabled 4. Add first-frame and/or last-frame image 5. Write your prompts 6. Generate ### Features For detailed feature description read the feature notes ## Usage combine videos This will just combine and post-process videos. 1. Select **Video Combining** on engine switch (this will disable the rendering section inside the backend) 2. Add up to 3 videos on the settings panel - (optional) Enable post-processing features, e.g. upscaling, marks,...) ## Shortcuts / Bookmarks | Numberkey | Description/Target | |----------:|-------------------:| |0 | Notes | |1 | Frontend with settings and inputs | |2 | Backend - main | |3 | Backend - post-processing | |4 | Backend - audio |
